Bring a medium #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @lemon{1}.

Once water is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%oz} to pot. Reduce to a low
simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender and floating to the top,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Reserve ¼ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Pat @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large
#pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sausage; cook, stirring frequently, until
browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; using a
#slotted spoon{}, transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While pasta cooks, heat @cream sauce base{4%oz}, @mushroom stock concentrate{2},
@garlic powder{1%tsp}, and juice from half the lemon in a large pan over medium-high
heat. Bring to a simmer, then stir in @spinach{5%oz}; cook until slightly wilted,
~{30-60%seconds}. Remove pan from heat.

Add drained tortelloni, half the @parmesan cheese{¼%cup}, and @butter{2%tbsp} to pan
with sauce; toss to coat. (TIP: If needed, stir in pasta cooking water 1 TBSP at
a time until pasta is coated in creamy sauce.) Taste and season with salt and
pepper.

Use pan used for sausage here. Add sausage along with drained tortelloni.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Serve with any
remaining lemon wedges on the side.

